Use **responsive design** with **CSS media queries**.

```css
/* Base styles for all devices */
body {
  font-size: 16px;
  margin: 0;
}

/* Tablets */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  body {
    font-size: 15px;
  }
}

/* Phones */
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  body {
    font-size: 14px;
  }
}
```

Common techniques:
- **Media queries**: apply different styles at different screen widths
- **Flexible layouts**: use **Flexbox** or **CSS Grid**
- **Relative units**: use `%`, `em`, `rem`, `vw`, `vh`
- **Responsive images**: `max-width: 100%; height: auto;`

Example with layout change:

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  gap: 20px;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}
```

Also include this in your HTML:

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

Use **responsive design** with **media queries** and **flexible layouts**.

```css
/* Base styles for all screens */
body {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: sans-serif;
}

.container {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem;
}

/* Tablets */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}

/* Phones */
@media (max-width: 480px) {
  body {
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .container {
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
}
```

Use:
- **Media queries** to apply styles at specific screen widths
- **Flexbox/Grid** for adaptable layouts
- **Relative units** like `%`, `rem`, `vw`, `vh`
- **Max-width** on images and containers

Also include this in your HTML for proper mobile scaling:

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```
